1
00:00:15,800 --> 00:00:16,960
Honey, my arm hurts.

2
00:00:17,280 --> 00:00:17,870
My arm broke.

3
00:00:17,870 --> 00:00:18,920
Easy.

4
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:20,670
What happened?

5
00:00:21,830 --> 00:00:23,280
Did they use torture on you?

6
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:25,600
You'll all get what's coming to you.

7
00:00:26,390 --> 00:00:28,440
She doesn't look innocent.

8
00:00:29,870 --> 00:00:31,440
There's a fresh cut on her palm.

9
00:00:31,860 --> 00:00:34,360
=Cases Between Us=

10
00:00:34,390 --> 00:00:35,430
Don't you think it's weird?

11
00:00:36,060 --> 00:00:37,488
=Episode 16=
Cello string!

12
00:00:37,504 --> 00:00:38,670
Why aren't you arresting her?

13
00:00:38,670 --> 00:00:39,632
Arrest her for what?

14
00:00:40,208 --> 00:00:42,000
Without evidence,
we'd have to let her go,

15
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:42,980
just like Zhang Chengcai.

16
00:00:42,992 --> 00:00:43,840
What do we do then?

17
00:00:45,632 --> 00:00:48,016
The address Zhang Chengcai gave
was the International Hotel.

18
00:00:48,080 --> 00:00:48,704
(Zhang Chengcai)

19
00:00:48,710 --> 00:00:51,900
(Home Address:
Room 306, International Hotel)

20
00:00:54,750 --> 00:00:55,920
They must be staying together.

21
00:00:56,500 --> 00:00:58,580
(International Hotel)

22
00:00:59,030 --> 00:01:00,200
Mr. Zhang and his family

23
00:01:00,200 --> 00:01:01,560
are staying in the top-floor suites.

24
00:01:01,560 --> 00:01:03,648
Rooms 305 and 306
are right across from each other.

25
00:01:03,920 --> 00:01:06,480
Mr. Zhang doesn't share a room
with Mei Fen?

26
00:01:06,480 --> 00:01:08,200
He stays in Room 306 by himself.

27
00:01:08,200 --> 00:01:09,100
His mother, Madam Zhang,

28
00:01:09,110 --> 00:01:11,040
(Manager Sun)
shares Room 305 with Miss Mei Fen.

29
00:01:13,280 --> 00:01:15,230
Do you have yesterday's
entry and exit records?

30
00:01:15,230 --> 00:01:15,790
Yes.

31
00:01:16,120 --> 00:01:16,910
The records.

32
00:01:24,384 --> 00:01:25,420
(10 AM)
Here they are.

33
00:01:25,640 --> 00:01:26,590
At 10 AM,

34
00:01:26,590 --> 00:01:28,560
Madam Zhang and Miss Mei Fen
left together.

35
00:01:28,560 --> 00:01:29,300
5:30 PM,

36
00:01:29,310 --> 00:01:30,640
(Room 306 Guest Zhang Chengcai)
Mr Zhang left.

37
00:01:30,640 --> 00:01:33,070
1 AM, Madam Zhang returned.

38
00:01:33,070 --> 00:01:35,400
3 AM, Miss Mei Fen returned.

39
00:01:35,408 --> 00:01:37,040
Mr. Zhang never returned.

40
00:01:38,352 --> 00:01:40,350
What's going on
with Madam Zhang and Mei Fen?

41
00:01:40,350 --> 00:01:42,144
Why are they out
until the middle of the night?

42
00:01:42,144 --> 00:01:43,640
That's our guests' privacy.

43
00:01:43,640 --> 00:01:44,790
We don't ask.

44
00:01:45,760 --> 00:01:47,480
Do they usually come and go together?

45
00:01:47,480 --> 00:01:48,040
Only yesterday.

46
00:01:48,040 --> 00:01:49,640
Madam Zhang came back alone.

47
00:01:50,070 --> 00:01:52,480
Did Mei Fen seem any different lately?

48
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:57,070
She usually dresses very elegantly.

49
00:01:57,070 --> 00:01:58,120
Yesterday, she went out

50
00:01:58,120 --> 00:01:59,870
in high heels and a qipao.

51
00:01:59,870 --> 00:02:01,590
But when she came back, she was wearing

52
00:02:01,590 --> 00:02:02,310
cloth shoes

53
00:02:02,310 --> 00:02:03,350
and coarse cotton trousers.

54
00:02:07,248 --> 00:02:08,840
(Yunxiu Pavilion)
As the saying goes,

55
00:02:08,840 --> 00:02:10,280
"Meng and Jiao are never apart."

56
00:02:10,280 --> 00:02:11,840
So why's one here

57
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:13,120
without the other today?

58
00:02:13,590 --> 00:02:14,800
Master Liang,

59
00:02:15,150 --> 00:02:16,750
can't I come

60
00:02:16,750 --> 00:02:18,360
just to see you?

61
00:02:18,360 --> 00:02:20,240
Do you believe that yourself?

62
00:02:22,030 --> 00:02:23,280
I'll get straight to it.

63
00:02:23,470 --> 00:02:24,840
I want to ask you about someone.

64
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:25,470
Who?

65
00:02:25,870 --> 00:02:26,710
Zhang Chengcai.

66
00:02:26,710 --> 00:02:28,480
One of the Four Young Masters
in Jingshi.

67
00:02:28,960 --> 00:02:30,400
He's one of the Four Young Masters?

68
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:32,120
That's what the newspapers call him.

69
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:34,710
He's seen courting

70
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:38,120
opera singers,

71
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:39,952
cabaret singers, or movie stars.

72
00:02:39,952 --> 00:02:41,560
Whoever's famous, he chases after her.

73
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:43,310
Then he takes her to Jingshi No. 1,

74
00:02:43,310 --> 00:02:45,310
tips off the reporters,
and lets them snap photos.

75
00:02:45,480 --> 00:02:47,710
He's always making the tabloids
with scandals.

76
00:02:50,560 --> 00:02:52,590
That's how he drums up business
for his restaurant.

77
00:02:52,590 --> 00:02:54,910
But compared to others...

78
00:02:55,590 --> 00:02:57,080
Anything in your storeroom

79
00:02:57,080 --> 00:02:58,280
could buy

80
00:02:58,280 --> 00:03:00,280
ten Jingshi No. 1 Restaurants.

81
00:03:02,120 --> 00:03:03,400
But the public doesn't know that.

82
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:05,216
To them, he's just another
spoiled rich kid.

83
00:03:05,232 --> 00:03:07,630
Otherwise, why would all those actresses
fall for him?

84
00:03:11,430 --> 00:03:12,840
I've risked my life

85
00:03:12,840 --> 00:03:14,470
trying to shake off that label.

86
00:03:14,592 --> 00:03:16,528
And he keeps putting it back on himself.

87
00:03:16,576 --> 00:03:18,030
What's so great about that reputation?

88
00:03:18,310 --> 00:03:20,120
How could Bai Lu fall
for a man like him?

89
00:03:21,904 --> 00:03:24,320
Zhang Chengcai and his mother
live at the International Hotel.

90
00:03:25,520 --> 00:03:27,030
Guess...

91
00:03:28,470 --> 00:03:29,470
who pays the bill?

92
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:33,190
Don't tell me it was Bai Lu.

93
00:03:34,672 --> 00:03:36,840
She wasn't even working.
Where did the money come from?

94
00:03:37,030 --> 00:03:38,030
Her reputation.

95
00:03:38,590 --> 00:03:40,030
Fame is money.

96
00:03:40,560 --> 00:03:43,630
Back when Bai Lu
was at the height of her fame,

97
00:03:43,792 --> 00:03:46,120
she got married
and held a lavish wedding banquet there,

98
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:48,280
inviting all the city's elite.

99
00:03:48,280 --> 00:03:49,840
It brought the hotel a lot of prestige.

100
00:03:49,840 --> 00:03:51,840
She also performed there

101
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:53,280
ten times for free.

102
00:03:53,710 --> 00:03:55,520
The ballroom

103
00:03:55,520 --> 00:03:56,680
was packed every night.

104
00:03:57,910 --> 00:04:00,840
Giving them two rooms was nothing.

105
00:04:03,590 --> 00:04:05,630
Didn't the Zhangs have a home?

106
00:04:05,630 --> 00:04:07,280
Why insist on living in a hotel?

107
00:04:07,960 --> 00:04:09,840
Well, that's a long story.

108
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:12,120
His mother is a widow.

109
00:04:12,384 --> 00:04:13,710
You know what that means?

110
00:04:13,870 --> 00:04:14,630
I do.

111
00:04:14,630 --> 00:04:15,470
Her husband died.

112
00:04:17,070 --> 00:04:17,920
She started

113
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:21,270
out selling breakfast
from a roadside stall,

114
00:04:21,270 --> 00:04:23,040
raising Zhang Chengcai all by herself.

115
00:04:23,310 --> 00:04:24,390
His father

116
00:04:24,390 --> 00:04:26,120
left them a small courtyard house
in Beijing.

117
00:04:26,390 --> 00:04:29,040
When Zhang Chengcai

118
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:30,270
turned sixteen,

119
00:04:30,270 --> 00:04:31,720
she sold the house

120
00:04:32,360 --> 00:04:33,750
and sent him abroad.

121
00:04:34,270 --> 00:04:36,680
He came back two years later
as a completely different man.

122
00:04:36,680 --> 00:04:37,680
Guess what he did?

123
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:41,390
He started pretending
to be a spoiled rich kid.

124
00:04:41,390 --> 00:04:43,510
Walked around every day
with a huge cigar in his mouth,

125
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:45,560
mixing with the rich and powerful.

126
00:04:45,560 --> 00:04:47,800
He actually made
quite a few wealthy friends.

127
00:04:47,872 --> 00:04:49,232
His mother opened this restaurant

128
00:04:49,360 --> 00:04:51,270
with their backing.

129
00:04:51,630 --> 00:04:53,120
After they struck it rich,

130
00:04:53,480 --> 00:04:57,000
they thought living in that
haunted house was beneath them.

131
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:59,120
That's why they moved
to the International Hotel.

132
00:05:01,870 --> 00:05:03,190
However, neither mother nor son

133
00:05:04,120 --> 00:05:05,680
has a head for business.

134
00:05:06,360 --> 00:05:08,120
The one running the restaurant

135
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:09,800
is their child bride,

136
00:05:10,120 --> 00:05:11,070
Mei Fen.

137
00:05:11,390 --> 00:05:12,390
I've got to admit,

138
00:05:12,390 --> 00:05:14,360
the Jingshi No. 1

139
00:05:16,310 --> 00:05:17,680
really does serve great food.

140
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:18,680
I went there twice.

141
00:05:20,144 --> 00:05:21,070
Worth the money.

142
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:25,360
Nothing gets past Master Liang.

143
00:05:25,680 --> 00:05:27,040
You know everything.

144
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:30,360
Bring that big lug with you next time.

145
00:05:30,360 --> 00:05:31,560
You'll learn even more.

146
00:05:39,780 --> 00:05:44,780
(Jingshi Police Department)

147
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:46,190
You're like a cat.

148
00:05:46,190 --> 00:05:47,560
Nobody knows where you are.

149
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:49,310
Didn't even bother filing for leave.

150
00:05:49,310 --> 00:05:50,630
You dumped the whole mess on me.

151
00:05:50,920 --> 00:05:51,600
Looks like

152
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:53,190
you managed just fine without me.

153
00:05:53,190 --> 00:05:55,070
Exactly.

154
00:05:56,190 --> 00:05:56,830
Right.

155
00:05:57,410 --> 00:05:58,160
Chief Yuan,

156
00:05:58,224 --> 00:06:01,040
if you'd come back one day later,
I'd have resigned.

157
00:06:01,310 --> 00:06:02,920
This department is full of talent.

158
00:06:02,920 --> 00:06:04,190
For example, Yang Dezhi.

159
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:06,680
You're being too modest.

160
00:06:06,680 --> 00:06:07,870
You've helped us a lot.

161
00:06:07,870 --> 00:06:09,950
We're a pretty good team.

162
00:06:09,950 --> 00:06:11,390
Alright, enough. Back to business.

163
00:06:11,390 --> 00:06:12,190
Something came up.

164
00:06:12,190 --> 00:06:14,270
I picked up a lead
on a member of the Longevity Sect.

165
00:06:14,270 --> 00:06:15,640
Longevity Pills
were too expensive,

166
00:06:15,650 --> 00:06:16,780
so they wanted to steal some.

167
00:06:16,790 --> 00:06:18,470
They tailed the people
handing out the pills

168
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:19,696
and ended up at a restaurant.

169
00:06:20,040 --> 00:06:20,950
Jingshi No. 1?

170
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:21,870
Smart.

171
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:22,870
Besides,

172
00:06:23,080 --> 00:06:25,190
the Longevity Sect

173
00:06:25,190 --> 00:06:27,630
has been Zhang Chengcai
and Madam Zhang's operation.

174
00:06:33,480 --> 00:06:35,000
This way, Misters.

175
00:06:36,070 --> 00:06:36,920
Have a seat.

176
00:06:39,270 --> 00:06:41,000
No wonder it's called Jingshi No. 1.

177
00:06:41,430 --> 00:06:42,510
Quite the establishment.

178
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:47,430
Mister,

179
00:06:47,430 --> 00:06:49,510
what can I get you today?

180
00:06:53,430 --> 00:06:54,360
Cantonese cuisine?

181
00:06:55,510 --> 00:06:56,390
Our chefs

182
00:06:56,390 --> 00:06:58,680
were brought in from Shunde.

183
00:06:58,680 --> 00:07:00,830
They're direct heirs
to the Taishi culinary tradition.

184
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:04,120
Great.

185
00:07:04,160 --> 00:07:06,680
Then I'll have a bowl of luzhu
[*Traditional Beijing street food]

186
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:08,070
and an order of stir-fried tripe.

187
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:09,240
Sir,

188
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:11,950
we only serve Cantonese food here.

189
00:07:11,950 --> 00:07:12,750
No such dishes?

190
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:15,630
That's false advertising.

191
00:07:15,950 --> 00:07:17,680
Go get your boss.

192
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:19,270
Uh...

193
00:07:23,740 --> 00:07:24,864
(Jingshi Police Department)

194
00:07:30,870 --> 00:07:31,510
Misters,

195
00:07:31,750 --> 00:07:32,270
just a moment.

196
00:07:32,560 --> 00:07:33,120
Just a moment.

197
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:40,360
The night-soil collector
hasn't shown up yet,

198
00:07:40,360 --> 00:07:42,630
and someone is already
lining up to taste it.

199
00:07:47,280 --> 00:07:49,560
What can I do for you?

200
00:07:51,904 --> 00:07:54,368
Where were you between ten last night
and three this morning?

201
00:07:57,328 --> 00:07:58,704
That's my privacy.

202
00:07:58,768 --> 00:08:00,190
Your whereabouts are unaccounted for.

203
00:08:00,190 --> 00:08:01,510
There are rope burns on your hands.

204
00:08:01,520 --> 00:08:02,750
When you returned to the hotel,

205
00:08:02,750 --> 00:08:04,920
you were lightly dressed
and covered in dust.

206
00:08:06,070 --> 00:08:07,160
We have reason to believe

207
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:08,800
you murdered Bai Lu.

208
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:13,360
You've got quite a mouth.

209
00:08:13,870 --> 00:08:15,190
No evidence?

210
00:08:16,720 --> 00:08:18,680
Is this how the police solve cases now?

211
00:08:18,680 --> 00:08:19,680
You want evidence?

212
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:21,720
Then tell us.

213
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,630
How did you get those rope burns?

214
00:08:24,680 --> 00:08:25,800
From work.

215
00:08:26,240 --> 00:08:27,120
Is that a crime?

216
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:30,390
If you're here to eat,

217
00:08:30,390 --> 00:08:31,950
you're more than welcome.

218
00:08:31,950 --> 00:08:34,270
If you're here looking for trouble,

219
00:08:34,304 --> 00:08:35,960
then I'm done with this conversation.

220
00:08:38,720 --> 00:08:39,960
A restaurant

221
00:08:40,480 --> 00:08:41,720
lives or dies by its reputation.

222
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:43,600
Yet you've got fake paintings,

223
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:44,870
fake imperial porcelain,

224
00:08:45,270 --> 00:08:46,240
and you claim your chef

225
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:47,910
is the best heir to Taishi cuisine.

226
00:08:48,480 --> 00:08:49,870
Who's his master?

227
00:08:49,870 --> 00:08:51,790
I don't recall anyone
from the Jiang family

228
00:08:51,790 --> 00:08:53,270
opening a restaurant in Beijing.

229
00:08:53,750 --> 00:08:54,360
Go.

230
00:08:54,360 --> 00:08:55,200
Bring him out.

231
00:08:55,408 --> 00:08:56,510
I'd like to talk to him.

232
00:08:57,670 --> 00:08:58,840
Please see yourselves out.

233
00:08:59,670 --> 00:09:01,720
Go make a scene somewhere else.

234
00:09:25,460 --> 00:09:27,220
(Jingshi No. 1)

235
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:29,200
Misters, this way.

236
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:30,790
Young Master Xiang, over here.

237
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:32,910
Easy now. Watch your step.

238
00:09:32,910 --> 00:09:34,790
- I'm not drunk.
- It's fine.

239
00:09:37,936 --> 00:09:39,080
What are you staring at?

240
00:09:42,320 --> 00:09:43,750
Trying to outdo me in shamelessness?

241
00:09:44,270 --> 00:09:46,510
I've never lost at that
since the day I was born.

242
00:09:47,870 --> 00:09:49,790
What's there to be proud of?

243
00:09:49,790 --> 00:09:50,480
I don't care.

244
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:51,200
I have to win.

245
00:09:55,870 --> 00:09:57,240
She's out.

246
00:09:59,720 --> 00:10:00,510
Cloth shoes.

247
00:10:00,510 --> 00:10:01,488
Coarse cotton trousers.

248
00:10:01,870 --> 00:10:02,790
Manager Sun said

249
00:10:02,790 --> 00:10:03,960
this was what she wore

250
00:10:03,960 --> 00:10:04,870
the night Bai Lu died.

251
00:10:23,790 --> 00:10:25,030
Come on.

252
00:10:25,030 --> 00:10:25,960
There's plenty to eat.

253
00:10:25,960 --> 00:10:26,550
Here.

254
00:10:26,550 --> 00:10:27,390
Take it.

255
00:10:27,550 --> 00:10:28,200
Slow down.

256
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:29,360
There's enough for everyone.

257
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:30,080
Lots of food.

258
00:10:30,080 --> 00:10:31,248
I have enough for everyone.

259
00:10:31,270 --> 00:10:32,120
Here.

260
00:10:43,270 --> 00:10:44,000
It's fine.

261
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:45,080
Go ahead and eat.

262
00:10:46,790 --> 00:10:48,120
Like a hound.

263
00:10:48,640 --> 00:10:49,910
You always manage to sniff me out.

264
00:10:50,320 --> 00:10:52,310
Only if there's a scent to follow.

265
00:10:52,310 --> 00:10:53,150
Right?

266
00:10:54,200 --> 00:10:55,670
So this is where you really live.

267
00:10:55,670 --> 00:10:57,240
What's it to you?

268
00:11:00,208 --> 00:11:02,240
You've been keeping secrets
from the Zhang family.

269
00:11:02,352 --> 00:11:04,750
What do you think Madam Zhang
would do if she found out?

270
00:11:06,870 --> 00:11:08,030
Maybe I should tell her

271
00:11:08,030 --> 00:11:08,960
about this place.

272
00:11:11,150 --> 00:11:13,000
So now you're threatening me?

273
00:11:17,240 --> 00:11:18,080
Wu.

274
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:20,550
Don't blame her.

275
00:11:20,550 --> 00:11:22,360
The house was damaged.

276
00:11:22,360 --> 00:11:24,390
She's only been coming back
at night to fix it.

277
00:11:24,390 --> 00:11:26,510
From now on, we won't let her
do it anymore. Okay?

278
00:11:33,870 --> 00:11:34,670
Little girl,

279
00:11:34,910 --> 00:11:35,910
let me ask you something.

280
00:11:36,288 --> 00:11:37,184
When did the big sister

281
00:11:37,870 --> 00:11:39,150
leave yesterday?

282
00:11:40,480 --> 00:11:42,150
She was exhausted,

283
00:11:42,150 --> 00:11:43,024
and she fell asleep.

284
00:11:43,030 --> 00:11:44,990
She didn't wake up
until the middle of the night.

285
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:45,790
She got scared

286
00:11:45,790 --> 00:11:47,360
and hurried back.

287
00:11:47,960 --> 00:11:48,790
Wu.

288
00:11:48,790 --> 00:11:49,390
Sit down.

289
00:11:49,840 --> 00:11:50,240
Eat.

290
00:11:50,240 --> 00:11:50,910
It's okay.

291
00:11:54,320 --> 00:11:57,240
So you got back to
the International Hotel at 3 AM?

292
00:11:57,550 --> 00:11:58,240
Yes.

293
00:12:02,910 --> 00:12:04,910
The window frame was loose.
You tied it with a rope.

294
00:12:06,240 --> 00:12:07,910
That's how you
got the marks on my hands.

295
00:12:08,270 --> 00:12:09,870
The roof tiles were broken.

296
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:11,270
So you were covered in dirt.

297
00:12:12,080 --> 00:12:12,750
Besides,

298
00:12:12,750 --> 00:12:14,200
the calluses on your hands

299
00:12:14,870 --> 00:12:17,120
and the way you stand,
your back's clearly worn out.

300
00:12:19,670 --> 00:12:21,480
You really do come back here
to work regularly.

301
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:23,000
So,

302
00:12:24,080 --> 00:12:25,390
does that clear my name?

303
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:28,670
But you had a motive.

304
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:32,240
You never hated Bai Lu, did you?

305
00:12:39,600 --> 00:12:40,320
My sister

306
00:12:42,440 --> 00:12:44,360
gave up a wealthy life

307
00:12:44,448 --> 00:12:45,550
and went against our parents

308
00:12:45,550 --> 00:12:46,840
to divorce my brother-in-law.

309
00:12:49,240 --> 00:12:49,670
Sometimes,

310
00:12:49,670 --> 00:12:51,030
women have so little say

311
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:56,870
over their own fate.

312
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:04,600
You've seen

313
00:13:05,240 --> 00:13:06,150
Zhang Chengcai.

314
00:13:07,150 --> 00:13:09,120
Who'd marry a man like that?

315
00:13:11,240 --> 00:13:12,080
You're right.

316
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:14,360
I never hated Bai Lu.

317
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:15,670
If anything,

318
00:13:16,720 --> 00:13:17,870
I was grateful to her.

319
00:13:19,790 --> 00:13:21,550
Because she married Zhang Chengcai.

320
00:13:22,750 --> 00:13:24,750
I finally had a little of the freedom

321
00:13:26,360 --> 00:13:28,270
I'd always wanted.

322
00:13:32,480 --> 00:13:33,270
But now

323
00:13:35,440 --> 00:13:36,550
she's gone.

324
00:13:45,150 --> 00:13:45,840
Mei Fen.

325
00:13:49,440 --> 00:13:50,928
You'll have that freedom someday.

326
00:13:53,790 --> 00:13:54,440
Thank you.

327
00:14:00,550 --> 00:14:02,200
Have you heard of the Longevity Sect?

328
00:14:05,440 --> 00:14:06,510
Longevity Sect.

329
00:14:09,670 --> 00:14:10,390
I have.

330
00:14:11,670 --> 00:14:13,360
But that's Madam Zhang's business.

331
00:14:14,750 --> 00:14:16,440
I only run Jingshi No. 1.

332
00:14:16,510 --> 00:14:17,960
I don't know much

333
00:14:18,256 --> 00:14:20,080
about the Zhang family's
other businesses.

334
00:14:29,480 --> 00:14:30,120
Go on.

335
00:14:30,630 --> 00:14:31,360
Is it good?

336
00:14:35,390 --> 00:14:36,000
Let's go.

337
00:14:38,360 --> 00:14:39,120
I won't see you out.

338
00:14:45,270 --> 00:14:48,200
Mei Fen's in the clear.

339
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:49,790
She has a solid alibi

340
00:14:49,790 --> 00:14:50,790
and no motive.

341
00:14:50,790 --> 00:14:51,720
It wasn't her.

342
00:14:52,480 --> 00:14:54,030
But she lied

343
00:14:54,030 --> 00:14:55,120
about the Longevity Sect.

344
00:14:56,550 --> 00:14:57,200
This is bad!

345
00:14:57,480 --> 00:14:58,360
Something's happened!

346
00:14:58,550 --> 00:14:59,870
Zhang Chengcai is dead!

347
00:15:02,360 --> 00:15:03,550
Let me tell you this.

348
00:15:03,776 --> 00:15:05,536
(Jingshi Police Department)
My son's body

349
00:15:05,552 --> 00:15:06,870
was covered in bruises.

350
00:15:07,150 --> 00:15:08,200
Not a single patch of skin

351
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:10,000
was left untouched.

352
00:15:10,750 --> 00:15:11,870
My son...

353
00:15:17,550 --> 00:15:18,790
Murderer!

354
00:15:19,120 --> 00:15:20,000
Murderer!

355
00:15:20,240 --> 00:15:21,120
Murderer!

356
00:15:21,120 --> 00:15:24,120
Give me back my son.

357
00:15:24,120 --> 00:15:26,790
He had my son beaten.

358
00:15:26,790 --> 00:15:28,240
My son couldn't live with it,

359
00:15:28,240 --> 00:15:28,910
and he

360
00:15:28,910 --> 00:15:30,840
(Madam Zhang)
took his own life...

361
00:15:30,840 --> 00:15:31,510
Madam Zhang,

362
00:15:31,510 --> 00:15:32,840
an accusation requires evidence.

363
00:15:32,840 --> 00:15:34,144
Your word alone isn't enough.

364
00:15:34,910 --> 00:15:35,600
Who are you?

365
00:15:35,792 --> 00:15:38,528
Yuan Hong, Chief of Division Four,
Jingshi Police Department.

366
00:15:38,544 --> 00:15:40,870
I'll take full responsibility
during this investigation.

367
00:15:40,870 --> 00:15:43,350
So, Chief Yuan, are you admitting
your men tortured the deceased?

368
00:15:43,360 --> 00:15:44,720
The deceased was the prime suspect

369
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:46,670
in Bai Lu's murder.

370
00:15:46,670 --> 00:15:48,240
Questioning him was entirely lawful.

371
00:15:49,270 --> 00:15:50,270
Cut the crap.

372
00:15:50,270 --> 00:15:51,630
You're used to abusing your power.

373
00:15:51,630 --> 00:15:53,390
Everyone, listen to what he said.

374
00:15:53,390 --> 00:15:54,720
Take a good look at this.

375
00:15:54,720 --> 00:15:56,440
Do you have any idea
what happened to my son?

376
00:15:56,630 --> 00:15:57,750
His whole body

377
00:15:57,750 --> 00:16:00,360
was covered in bruises.

378
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:01,720
They beat him so badly

379
00:16:01,720 --> 00:16:05,080
that he could barely walk.

380
00:16:05,080 --> 00:16:05,750
Fine.

381
00:16:05,750 --> 00:16:06,870
If that's true,

382
00:16:07,480 --> 00:16:08,600
then let us examine the body.

383
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:09,790
What else is there to examine?

384
00:16:09,872 --> 00:16:10,896
My son was perfectly fine.

385
00:16:10,896 --> 00:16:12,550
But how did he come home
and commit suicide

386
00:16:12,550 --> 00:16:14,000
after you questioned him?

387
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:15,360
Answer me! Answer!

388
00:16:15,360 --> 00:16:17,150
If your son were murdered,

389
00:16:17,480 --> 00:16:18,120
as his mother,

390
00:16:18,120 --> 00:16:20,240
shouldn't your first concern
be finding his killer?

391
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:22,464
And if he took his own life,
why won't you let the police

392
00:16:22,512 --> 00:16:23,320
perform an autopsy?

393
00:16:23,790 --> 00:16:25,120
Unless you had something to do

394
00:16:25,370 --> 00:16:26,390
with his death.

395
00:16:35,390 --> 00:16:36,600
Did you all hear that?

396
00:16:37,120 --> 00:16:38,910
Is that something

397
00:16:38,910 --> 00:16:40,120
a police officer

398
00:16:40,120 --> 00:16:42,630
should say?

399
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:43,790
My son.

400
00:16:44,120 --> 00:16:45,670
My own flesh and blood.

401
00:16:46,240 --> 00:16:48,600
I gave birth to him.

402
00:16:48,600 --> 00:16:50,240
Now my son is dead,

403
00:16:50,600 --> 00:16:53,240
and he's trying to pin it on me.

404
00:16:53,240 --> 00:16:56,120
Who says something like that?

405
00:16:56,670 --> 00:17:00,600
Heavens!

406
00:17:02,320 --> 00:17:04,680
I was widowed for twenty years.

407
00:17:05,160 --> 00:17:08,720
I raised my son all by myself.

408
00:17:09,160 --> 00:17:11,270
Do you know how hard that was?

409
00:17:11,270 --> 00:17:12,680
And now these policemen

410
00:17:12,680 --> 00:17:16,510
drove him to death.

411
00:17:16,544 --> 00:17:17,240
Take the picture.

412
00:17:17,550 --> 00:17:18,510
All of you!

413
00:17:18,720 --> 00:17:20,110
Get his face.

414
00:17:20,720 --> 00:17:23,830
- Let everyone in Beijing see his face.
- Stop taking pictures.

415
00:17:23,830 --> 00:17:26,240
Look at

416
00:17:26,240 --> 00:17:27,470
these unformed beasts.

417
00:17:27,480 --> 00:17:28,790
Did the police abuse their power?

418
00:17:28,790 --> 00:17:29,440
My son.

419
00:17:29,440 --> 00:17:31,232
Is the police department
covering up torture

420
00:17:31,248 --> 00:17:32,720
and protecting brutal officers
who persecute the people?

421
00:17:32,720 --> 00:17:33,870
- That's right, Chief Yuan.
- Yes!

422
00:17:33,880 --> 00:17:35,400
Where's the justice?

423
00:17:35,680 --> 00:17:37,310
Where's the law?

424
00:17:37,310 --> 00:17:37,920
Back up.

425
00:17:37,920 --> 00:17:38,400
Quiet.

426
00:17:39,400 --> 00:17:39,960
Quiet.

427
00:17:39,960 --> 00:17:40,590
Take the picture.

428
00:17:40,760 --> 00:17:41,480
What are you doing?

429
00:17:41,480 --> 00:17:41,900
Chief Yuan.

430
00:17:41,920 --> 00:17:42,680
What are you doing?

431
00:17:42,680 --> 00:17:44,720
What's all this commotion?

432
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:47,264
(Jingshi Police Department)
Do you think this is a marketplace?

433
00:17:51,790 --> 00:17:53,000
You two again.

434
00:17:53,310 --> 00:17:54,880
Can you stop causing trouble for once?

435
00:17:55,750 --> 00:17:56,200
I...

436
00:17:57,200 --> 00:18:00,510
Heavens!

437
00:18:00,790 --> 00:18:01,200
Please!

438
00:18:01,440 --> 00:18:04,240
You have to give me justice.

439
00:18:04,920 --> 00:18:05,830
It was them.

440
00:18:06,550 --> 00:18:08,920
They beat my son to death.

441
00:18:08,920 --> 00:18:11,550
My own son.

442
00:18:12,310 --> 00:18:14,030
Commissioner, that's not what happened.

443
00:18:14,030 --> 00:18:15,350
The autopsy hasn't started yet.

444
00:18:15,350 --> 00:18:16,384
Autopsy? Huh?

445
00:18:16,432 --> 00:18:18,550
The public is already at our doorstep.

446
00:18:18,550 --> 00:18:20,110
Did either of you report this to me?

447
00:18:20,350 --> 00:18:21,640
And now the press is here, too.

448
00:18:21,640 --> 00:18:22,200
This...

449
00:18:22,880 --> 00:18:25,510
What do you expect this looks like
for the police department?

450
00:18:25,824 --> 00:18:26,750
Young Master Zhao.

451
00:18:27,720 --> 00:18:28,880
I'm revoking

452
00:18:29,110 --> 00:18:32,000
your appointment
as Special Investigative Consultant

453
00:18:32,400 --> 00:18:34,680
effective immediately.

454
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:35,530
Please don't...

455
00:18:35,550 --> 00:18:38,350
If I prove his death had nothing to do
with the police,

456
00:18:42,030 --> 00:18:42,830
will he get

457
00:18:42,830 --> 00:18:44,110
his position back?

458
00:18:51,110 --> 00:18:52,110
Go ahead and find out.

459
00:18:52,320 --> 00:18:53,240
I will.

460
00:18:53,240 --> 00:18:53,960
If I can't,

461
00:18:53,960 --> 00:18:54,960
I'll resign.

462
00:18:54,960 --> 00:18:56,200
You said it.

463
00:18:56,670 --> 00:18:57,830
Everyone here heard you.

464
00:18:58,288 --> 00:19:00,256
Just wait.
You'll be stripped of your post

465
00:19:00,350 --> 00:19:01,310
and dragged into court.

466
00:19:05,140 --> 00:19:07,420
(End of Episode 16)

467
00:19:08,280 --> 00:19:09,920
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

468
00:19:09,920 --> 00:19:11,460
♪Troubled times
are but a laughing matter♪

469
00:19:11,460 --> 00:19:12,710
♪However, the world changes♪

470
00:19:12,710 --> 00:19:14,630
♪You'll still be by my side♪

471
00:19:14,630 --> 00:19:16,320
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

472
00:19:16,320 --> 00:19:17,890
♪Praise and blame come and go♪

473
00:19:17,890 --> 00:19:19,460
♪If this is my final chapter♪

474
00:19:19,460 --> 00:19:21,960
♪I'll solve this mystery with you♪
